    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://chicago.craigslist.org/wcl/fbh/6042147064.html"></div>
        </div>
Welcome to your neighborhood sports bar. Pull up a stool. Watch the game. Or, take on the world's greatest courses on our new HD golf simulators.<br>
<br>
Tap In Pub &amp; Carvery has a bigger bar and 15 TV's tuned to the best sporting events of the day. On the tapper, more beers, eight to be exact, including many of the hottest craft beers around (and constantly rotating in the best and buzziest). The menu is still all about flavorful pub food, and we've added a few new items that are sure to make your go-to list.<br>
<br>
Play golf year round on the world's best courses -- Pebble Beach, St Andrews, Rich Harvest Farms, and more - all in realistic HD, the best anywhere. Whether you're an avid golfer, an enthusiastic duffer, or someone just looking for a fun outing with friends and family, you can't beat the experience of HD golf.<br>
<br>
Our HD golf simulators are certain to liven up any business luncheon, team building event, or social gathering. Our spacious and private dining area can accommodate up to 40 guests in a variety of table arrangements and extends seamlessly into the pub.<br>
<br>
As a Tap In Pub &amp; Carvery Restaurant General Manager you will own the overall 4-wall business. You will partner with the Chef to ensure front of house operations are aligned with the culinary program in your location. You will maintain a clean, physical space, inspire and maintain high team morale and standards. You are the driver!<br>
<br>
You are responsible for building your team, coaching for success, and developing your associates into the leaders of the future. You are fully accountable for all systems, people and standards within the restaurant.<br>
<br>
Although you won't often be creating the food, it is expected you will know as much about the menu as our culinary team. You place passion and pride behind bringing inspired food and drink to thousands of Guests a week, and ensuring your team brings it to life in your restaurant.<br>
<br>
Responsibilities:<br>
-Managing the floor and flow of business, role modeling and upholding standards, dress code and operating systems and standards in the Front of House.<br>
-Coaching your associates on a daily basis for development and success.<br>
-Driving sales and local restaurant marketing initiatives to build business.<br>
-Guest and staff relations and serious disciplinary action.<br>
-Manager and hourly staff development.<br>
-Physical plant maintenance.<br>
-Expert Scheduling<br>
-Recruitment<br>
-Follow up on all departments (food, bar, ops and people) financial goals, goal achievement and action plans.<br>
-General staff meetings and direct line meetings.<br>
-Accountable for business planning for the restaurant, key financials and KPI's, as well as maintaining and growing sales and profitability.<br>
<br>
Requirements:<br>
-Minimum 5 years hospitality industry experience in a self-directed leadership role.<br>
-Degree or Diploma in Hospitality or Business Management and/or proven personal commitment to professional development an asset.<br>
-Proven success with both people development in leadership positions and long-term sales growth.<br>
-Proven ability to achieve results through others.<br>
-Demonstrate ability to attract and retain excellent performers and to develop high performing teams.<br>
-Leadership and communication: has a leadership style that is developmental vs. policing, promotes a culture of dialogue, role models values and practices of the company.<br>
-Proven entrepreneurial spirit through having presence "on the floor" and in the community.<br>
<br>
We are an equal opportunity employer and make employment decisions without regard to age, race, religion, national origin, gender, disability, veteran status, genetic information, sexual orientation and gender identity or any other protected class. Our locations are drug-free and pre-employment drug tests are required. <br>
<br>
Background checks are also required before employment begins.<br>
<br>
We participate in E-Verify and those who are ineligible to work in the United States will not be considered.<br>
<br>
